2. DEFINITION/GLOSSARY

¬†

Terms, abbreviations and acronyms

Meaning

Vampire Frontend

used by pawn shop outlet staff for day-to-day operations. This includes activity such as:

¬∑       Processing renewals and redemptions

¬∑       Enquiry pawners and tickets

¬∑       Report lost pledge

Status ‚ÄòU‚Äô

¬∑       When a ticket (grant) is newly created, a record is stored in the database with status 'U'

¬∑       When a ticket is renewed, a new record associated with the renewed ticket is also stored in the database with status 'U'.

 

Status ‚ÄòO‚Äô

When a ticket that was previously seized by the police is returned, its status is updated to 'O'

Status ‚ÄòR‚Äô

When a ticket is either renewed or redeemed, its status is updated to 'R'

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

3. BUSINESS CONTEXT

3.1. Project Overview

ValueMax aims to revamp its legacy Desktop Application into a Web Application. As part of the initial phase, this project focuses on assessing and documenting the current system to establish a clear understanding before proposing future improvements.

Action Logic: Renew ticket(s)

 

 

Trigger:

  • User fills in Ticket No and press Enter

1. Pre Checks:

  • Ticket Number must be entered
  • Ticket Number must exist in database
  • Ticket status must be U/O
  • PawnDate must be different from the current date
  • PIN must be associated with the entered staff code

¬†

2. Action Logic:

Condition

System Action

State Change

Ticket number is valid

Display ticket information in the table

State = "Data Shown"

Ticket number is invalid

Display error message

State unchanged

User presses Enter (after info is shown)

Display Payment form

Awaiting Payment

Collected Amount < Total Amount

Show error: "Collected Amount must be equal or greater than Total Amount"

State unchanged

Collected Amount ‚â• Total Amount

Proceed to PIN confirmation

Awaiting PIN Confirmation

Valid staffcode and PIN

Proceed to finalize renewal, print receipt [7.1.1] and contract [7.1.2], update ticket records

Status = Renewed

Invalid staffcode or PIN

Show error message

State unchanged

¬†

¬†

¬†

3. Post Flow:

  • UI: Proceeds to print receipt
  • Database:

o   Change current ticket status to 'R' (Renewed)

o   Insert a new ticket associated with the current one, with a status of 'U'

  • Valid Staff Code and PIN must be entered.
  • Redeemer must be the Pawner

Action Logic: Create New Customer

Trigger:

¬∑       User selects ‚ÄúOther‚Äù at the Redeemer form and enters a customer ID that does not exist in the system.

1. Pre Checks:

  • Entered ID must not exist in the customer database.
  • Customer and Guarantor information must be collected according to form validation rules.

¬†

2. Action Logic:

Condition

System Action

State Change

ID does not exist in database

Display Customer Details form

State = "Form Displayed"

Fill all mandatory fields in Customer section

Validate inputs in Customer section

State = "Customer Validating"

Errors in Customer section

Show error message

State unchanged

Customer has Guarantor = Yes

Display Guarantor section

State = "Guarantor Entry"

Fill all mandatory fields in Guarantor section

Validate inputs in Guarantor section

State = "Guarantor Validating"

Errors in Guarantor section

Show error message

State unchanged

Click "Update" button with valid Customer/Guarantor data

Save new customer to waterloo_march2025.pawner

State = "Customer Saved"

¬†

¬†

¬†

3. Post Flow:

  • UI:
    • Display success message
    • Redirect back to Redeemer form.
  • Database: Insert new record into waterloo_march2025.pawner.
